Aboro rice
saffron
4-5 scoops marrow
chopped onions
salt
vermouth
good stock at boiling point
butter
parmesean
olive oil

ladel hot stock over safron

with pairing knife, remove marrow from bones. 

in olive oil, reduce marrow slowly. salt and add onions. add some stock and add rice. toast rice. 
add vermouth reduce heat and start to add stock. at the end, add the soaked safron.
remove from heat.
add butter and cheese.

garnish:
lemon rind
chopped garlic
chopped parsly

Top with Ossobuco!!!!
